the population of Canada. Drawing on the results of a large research project that examined co-operatives in communities from coast to coast to coast, Co-operative Canada reveals how Canadians are using the co-operative model to collectively respond to the forces of globalization through local, community-owned enterprises. It does this through specific examples that vividly describe the pragmatic realities of the communities these co-ops serve.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunity developmentzCanadavCase studies. 0aCooperative societieszCanadavCase studies. 0aSocial entrepreneurshipzCanadavCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Regional Studies.2bisacsh1 aBrown, Leslie H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarrier, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColeman, William D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiamantopoulos, Mitch, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobrohoczki, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFairbairn, Brett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFairbairn, Brett, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFindlay, Isobel M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFulton, Murray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGingras, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGirard, Jean-Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeit, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKetilson, Lou Hammond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLanglois, Geneviève, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.